Mean-Opinion Score (MOS) Test

Measuring quality of synthesized speech

Thank you so much for participating in this test!

First listen to the 3 real-world samples and assume they have the score of 10 in all metric mentioned below. For better results, please wear headphones and stay in a quite environment. For each audio, provide a value from 1 to 10 to evaluate:

  • The general quality of the song, i.e. how much the song snippet sounds like noise or as a snippet from a real song (listen to a few provided real song samples to get the idea, assume they have the perfect score).
  • The coherence between the instruments, i.e., how much the instruments go well together in terms of rhythm and melody.

In total, there are five compared models and there are 15 samples from each model.

NB: Samples from compared systems are randomly shuffled. We suggest you first listen to the real-examples at the starting and then give scores for better comparison. You are allowed to replay samples as you want. Please remember to click the "Submit" button after finishing.

Section 2: Partial Generation

Measuring quality of inpainted and mixture audio

The task is music impainting. It means that the model is given some ground truth instrumental tracks and has to generate the remaining sources in a consistent and pleasantly sounding way.

For each question, the title indicates what instrumental tracks need to be generated (e.g., if the title says guitar-bass, it means that the model is given drums and piano tracks and has to generate consistent guitar and bass). You will first listen to the given condition music(e.g. drum+piano). Then the real impainted music (guitar+bass) is provided, and so as the real mixture (impainted + condition). That’s just a clue for you to know what is a reasonable sample to generate.

Then there are a few models for you to evaluate. For each model, you should listen to the impainted audio and the mixture audio. The impainted audio is the generated guitar+bass in the above example, given the condition music containing drums and piano you listened to before. The mixture audio is the impainted music + condition music, which is for you to listen to the piece and determine if they are consistent in melody and harmony.

For each question and each model, evaluate

  • The density of the partial generation (whether all requested instruments have been generated and for how long
  • The quality of the partial generation, how does the generated instruments match the condition audio? Do they sound they should be mixed together to form a piece of music?
